ADVANCED VIVA – Salesforce Custom Application (Assignment 09)
❓1. What is Salesforce and why is it called CRM?
✔ Answer:

Salesforce is a cloud-based CRM (Customer Relationship Management) platform used to manage customer data, sales, service, and business processes.

👉 It is called CRM because it helps in:

Tracking customer interactions
Managing leads and opportunities
Improving customer relationships
❓2. What is the difference between Standard Objects and Custom Objects?
✔ Answer:
Standard Objects → Predefined by Salesforce
Example: Account, Contact
Custom Objects → Created by user
Example: Student__c, Course__c

👉 Custom objects are used for specific business needs.

❓3. What is the significance of “__c” in object/field names?
✔ Answer:

“__c” indicates that the object/field is custom created.

Example:

Student__c → Custom object
Name → Standard field
❓4. What is a Lookup Relationship?
✔ Answer:

A Lookup relationship:

Links two objects
Does NOT enforce dependency

👉 Example:
Student → Course
Student can exist without Course

❓5. Difference between Lookup and Master-Detail Relationship?
✔ Answer:
Feature	Lookup	Master-Detail
Dependency	Optional	Mandatory
Deletion	Independent	Cascade delete
Security	Separate	Inherited
Roll-up fields	Not supported	Supported
❓6. Why did you use Lookup instead of Master-Detail?
✔ Answer:

Because:

Student can exist without Course
No strict dependency required

👉 Hence Lookup is more flexible.

❓7. What is Schema in Salesforce?
✔ Answer:

Schema defines:

Objects
Fields
Relationships

👉 It represents database structure.

❓8. What is App in Salesforce?
✔ Answer:

A Salesforce App is a collection of tabs (objects) designed for a specific purpose.

👉 Example:
Student Management App includes:

Students
Courses
Colleges
❓9. What is Lightning App?
✔ Answer:

Lightning App is a modern UI-based application that:

Supports dynamic interaction
Works on desktop & mobile
❓10. What is a Lightning Component?
✔ Answer:

Reusable UI component built using:

HTML (markup)
JavaScript
Apex (backend)

👉 Used to create dynamic UI.

❓11. What is Aura Framework?
✔ Answer:

Aura is a component-based framework used in Salesforce Lightning.

👉 It allows:

Reusable components
Event-driven architecture
❓12. What is the role of Apex in your application?
✔ Answer:

Apex is used for:

Backend logic
Data processing
Trigger execution
❓13. What is a Trigger in Salesforce?
✔ Answer:

Trigger is Apex code that runs:

Before/After insert, update, delete

👉 Used for automation.

❓14. What is Flow in Salesforce?
✔ Answer:

Flow is a no-code automation tool used to:

Automate processes
Update records
Send emails
❓15. Difference between Flow and Apex?
✔ Answer:
Flow	Apex
No code	Requires coding
Easy	Complex
Limited logic	Advanced logic
❓16. What is a Validation Rule?
✔ Answer:

Validation Rule:

Ensures correct data input
Prevents invalid records

👉 Example:
Total Amount cannot be blank

❓17. What is Page Layout?
✔ Answer:

Defines:

Field arrangement
UI display

👉 Controls user interface.

❓18. What is Record Type?
✔ Answer:

Record Type:

Allows different layouts for same object
Supports different business processes
❓19. What is SOQL?
✔ Answer:

Salesforce Object Query Language used to:

Fetch data from database

Example:

SELECT Name FROM Student__c
❓20. What is Governor Limit?
✔ Answer:

Limits enforced by Salesforce to:

Control resource usage
Maintain multi-tenant environment

👉 Example:
Max 100 SOQL queries

❓21. What is Multi-tenancy?
✔ Answer:

Multiple users share same resources but data is isolated.

❓22. What is Report in Salesforce?
✔ Answer:

Reports are used to:

Analyze data
Generate insights
❓23. What is Dashboard?
✔ Answer:

Visual representation of reports using:

Charts
Graphs
❓24. Why your report type was not showing Course?
✔ Answer:

Because:

Relationship not properly recognized
Or report type not configured with related object
❓25. What is Custom Report Type?
✔ Answer:

User-defined report structure that defines:

Object relationships
Fields available for reporting
❓26. What is Deployment Status?
✔ Answer:
In Development → Only admin can see
Deployed → Available to all users
❓27. What is App Launcher?
✔ Answer:

Menu to access:

Apps
Objects
❓28. Why your objects were not visible initially?
✔ Answer:

Because:

Not added to app navigation
Or profile permission issue
❓29. What is Field-Level Security?
✔ Answer:

Controls:

Who can see/edit fields
❓30. What is Role Hierarchy?
✔ Answer:

Defines data access based on:

Organization hierarchy
🔥 TRICK QUESTIONS (VERY IMPORTANT)
❓31. What happens if you delete a Course record?
✔ Answer:

In Lookup:

Student record remains
Course field becomes NULL
❓32. Why didn’t you use Master-Detail?
✔ Answer:

Because:

It enforces strict dependency
Not required in this case
❓33. Can one student have multiple courses?
✔ Answer:

Yes, but requires:

Junction Object (Many-to-Many relationship)
❓34. What is Junction Object?
✔ Answer:

Intermediate object used to connect:

Two objects in many-to-many relationship
❓35. Why Salesforce uses cloud architecture?
✔ Answer:
No local setup
Scalable
Accessible anywhere
✅ FINAL VIVA TIP

When answering:
👉 Use keywords:

Cloud-based
Scalable
Secure
Customizable
Multi-tenant